{
  "local_port": 34328,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I poke someone on Facebook?",
  "response": "Poking someone on Facebook is a simple way to get their attention or just say hello in a fun, casual way. Here's how you can do it:\n\n### On Desktop:\n1. **Log in to Facebook**: Go to [Facebook](https://www.facebook.com) and log into your account.\n2. **Go to the Person's Profile**: Search for the person you'd like to poke and click on their profile.\n3. **Find the Poke Button**: On their profile, look for the three dots (`\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7`) next to the \"Message\" button. Click on it to see the options.\n4. **Click \"Poke\"**: Select the \"Poke\" option from the dropdown menu.\n5. **Confirm**: If prompted, confirm that you\u2019d like to poke them.\n\n### On Mobile App:\n1. **Open the Facebook App**: Launch the Facebook app on your device and log in if needed.\n2. **Search for the Person**: Use the search bar to find the person you want to poke. Tap on their profile to open it.\n3. **Find the Poke Button**: Look for the three dots (`\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7`) or a \"More\" option on their profile. Tap it.\n4. **Select \"Poke\"**: Choose the \"Poke\" option from the menu.\n5. **Confirm**: If prompted, confirm your action.\n\n### Things to Note:\n- **Reciprocal Pokes**: If the person pokes you back, a new poke button will appear on their profile for future pokes.\n- **Notifications**: The person will receive a notification saying you poked them.\n- **Poke History**: You can view the people you\u2019ve poked or who\u2019ve poked you by going to the **Pokes page**. To find it:\n  - On desktop: Click the search bar and type \"Pokes.\"\n  - On mobile: Tap on the menu (\u2630), scroll down, and select \"See More,\" then tap \"Pokes.\"\n\nPoking is a lighthearted feature, so use it for fun and friendly interactions!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
